args: Heh heh heh. I can already imagine the\nuses for a toy like this. How greedy of you\nto try and keep it all for yourself, Augus!
That won't do. No, it won't do at all.\nI will be taking a piece of this for myself.\nHeh heh... Aaaaah ha ha ha ha!
I'm home, Ilia! That was quite the success.
Oh, hey, Mom. Welcome back.\nEr, and WHAT was a success, exactly?
Your creations! The people loved them.\nI heard more than one call you a genius.

Like that strange canister that gives a burst
of light when you throw it? The children
were just beside themselves with glee.
Your alchemy really is quite popular.
Well, I'm glad it's getting the reviews\nit so richly deserves.
No, I am! It means my alchemy's being\nuseful, right? Who could ask for more?
But I guess the opinions of random \nstrangers aren't as important to me\nas certain other things. That's all.
Are you back at that recipe again?

I'll never give it up, Meene; it's what my
parents left me. ...Be nice if it wasn't full
of gaps and unintelligible bits, but hey,
what's a girl gonna do?
You simply cannot leave a mystery be.\nYou've been so ever since you were a girl.
And you think research into other worlds\nis too dangerous and have told me so a\nmillion times SINCE I was a little girl!
You there. Silver-haired girl.\nAre you Ilia, the alchemist?
Here's a question for you, jarhead:\nEver heard of knocking before barging\ninto a lady's humble abode?
Criminals merit no such courtesy.\nYou are to answer for violating the peace\nwith your precious alchemy.
I have no idea what you're on about.
Feigning innocence, eh? That won't do.\nNo, it won't do at all.
An alchemical weapon was used in a\nterrorist attack in the city a few days ago.
Further investigation revealed that it\nwas developed by your parents.
Your parents researched the military\napplications of alchemy until the day\nthey absconded with their work.
They were hunted down and slain for their\ntreason, and their work recovered...\nleaving only a daughter behind.
And you're suggesting I used a weapon\nthey invented as a way of getting revenge\nagainst the military?
Avenging one's parents is a tired clich√©,\nbut it makes for a fine motive.
You're lying. My parents would never\nconstruct tools of war.
Neither me NOR my parents would allow\nour alchemy to be used to hurt people.
I have not come to hear your excuses.\nYou can shout them at the prison walls\nonce we have you in chains.
THIS is why I hate military types...\nOkay, fine. You wanna go? Let's go!
Your valor is most impressive, but I am\nafraid it won't do. No, it won't do at all.\nStop and have a look around, hmm?
I'm sorry, Ilia. I was careless. Oh, but it\npains me to be a liability to you like this!
Not another word, if you value your life.\nNow then, I am certain a genius alchemist\nlike you can read the writing on the wall?
You're a damn coward. ...But fine.\nI won't resist. Let her go.
Heh heh heh... Aaaaah ha ha ha ha!\nOh, but working with a genius is such a\npleasure. Always so quick on the uptake!
Alchemist Ilia! I, Logius, hereby arrest you\nfor the high crimes of violence against the\npeople and the disruption of order!
OW, geez! I'm a lady, you jerk! I mean,\nsince you've clearly never handled one\nof those before!
Ugh, this is the WORST. I have no idea\nwhat's even happening...
